author: @DataProfessor
text: Ken, Great video and insights on preparing a strong resume! Agreed that documentation is a plus for potential employers, a well documented code/notebook goes a long way in reproducibility of data science projects. Speaking of making websites and hosting on GitHub, Hugo (https://gohugo.io/) is a great tool, it is a static site generator that automatically creates a website directly from markdown files and it could be hosted on the github.io. Best of all, there's a large selection of themes to select from. Personally, I use it to create our research group's website http://codes.bio/
